heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 4th ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 16.2mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  9.2mm of rain fell during the storm's 5.3 hours length.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.
